text: Dubrava () is a rural locality (a village) in Taptykovsky Selsoviet, Ufimsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 180 as of 2010. There is 1 street. == Geography == It is located 30 km from Ufa, 8 km from Taptykovo. == References == Category:Rural localities in Ufimsky District
title: Dubrava, Republic of Bashkortostan
